The paper deals with a data structure for processing $nca$ and $link$ operations on a forest, which is a classic problem in data structures. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is the most likely category. The paper also mentions the application of the algorithm in finding maximum weight matching on a general graph, which falls under cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry). The paper also involves analyzing the time complexity of the algorithm, which is related to cs.LG (Computational Complexity) and cs.DL (Digital Libraries).
